RIFTSMUD STAFF ONBOARDING

Welcome to the RiftsMUD wizard staff. This is not the old Nightmare
immortal track. Roles are assigned by an Admin and gated by staff tools.

FIRST STEPS
1. Read the staff overview: help staff *wizard staff
2. Read your role handbook (Admin, Domain, Coding, or Roleplay)
3. Type workroom to reach your workspace
4. Type read book for a short in-room summary

ROLE HANDBOOKS (help <topic> *wizard staff)
  staff      overview of all four roles
  admin      head admin duties and tools
  domain     domain coordination and dominate staff
  coding     QCS/build workflow and realm layout
  roleplay   skills, tattoos, and request mailbox

YOUR ROLE IS SET BY POSITION
  arch / head arch  -> Admin
  domain_wiz        -> Domain
  creator           -> Coding
  rp_wiz            -> Roleplay

LPC BASICS
If you are new to LPC, read help ed *creator general and the tutorials
under /doc/build/room/ and /doc/build/monster/. Those files are generic
NM3 references; follow your role handbook for Rifts-specific paths and
permissions.

C89 REQUIRED
All LPC must use C89-style declarations for FluffOS 2.9. See the Coding
handbook for the short list.

DO NOT USE OUTDATED PATHS
  Player saves: /secure/save/users/<letter>/<name>.o
  QCS sandbox:  /realms/<yourname>/area/
  Game world:   /domains/Praxis/ and other /domains/ areas
  Old refs to /doc/LAW, /doc/BALANCE, /doc/QC do not exist on this lib.

WHEN YOU ARE READY
Contact your Domain wizard or an Admin to confirm your assigned directories
and tasks.

SEE ALSO
  help staff *wizard staff
